+# ADR-0001-conventions-units-sign
+
+## Status
+Accepted
+
+## Upstream references
+- ECO-0001: `cpa-architecture/docs/adr/ECO-0001-conventions-units.md` (as of 2026-02-16)
+- ECO-0004: `cpa-architecture/docs/adr/ECO-0004-repository-roles-boundaries.md` (as of 2026-02-16)
+
+## Decision summary (local)
+`cpa-sim` uses a single conventions contract for units, FFT/sign semantics, and stage-level metadata so every stage backend produces compatible `PulseState` data and deterministic outputs across runs.
+
+## Local instructions
+- Keep canonical state models under `src/cpa_sim/models/`; do not create backend-specific unit/sign conventions in stage modules.
+- Document and enforce units in config/state fields for time, frequency, energy, and wavelength.
+- Any sign convention change for chirp/dispersion/phase must include updates to physics golden tests and a `STATUS.md` entry.
+- Backends in `src/cpa_sim/stages/**` must adapt to this repo contract at the stage boundary rather than leaking third-party solver conventions.
+- Validation minimum for convention changes: `python -m pytest -q -m "not slow and not physics" --durations=10` and `python -m pytest -q -m physics --durations=10`.
+
+## Applies to
+- `src/cpa_sim/models/`
+- `src/cpa_sim/stages/`
+- `configs/examples/`
+- `tests/`
+- `STATUS.md`
+
+## Out of scope for this repo
+- Ecosystem-wide rationale and policy governance in ECO-0001.
+- Conventions for non-CPA repos (`phys-pipeline`, `cpa-testbench`, `abcdef-sim`).
+
+## Acceptance checks
+- [ ] `python -m pytest -q -m "not slow and not physics" --durations=10`
+- [ ] `python -m pytest -q -m physics --durations=10`
+- [ ] `python -m mypy src`
+- [ ] `python -m pre_commit run -a`
+
+## Migration notes
+Adopt immediately for new stages and backend adapters. For legacy code, migrate to shared model-level conventions before introducing new backends.
