+# ADR-0002-stage-interface-and-provenance
+
+## Status
+Accepted
+
+## Upstream references
+- ECO-0002: `cpa-architecture/docs/adr/ECO-0002-result-schema-contract.md` (as of 2026-02-16)
+- ECO-0004: `cpa-architecture/docs/adr/ECO-0004-repository-roles-boundaries.md` (as of 2026-02-16)
+
+## Decision summary (local)
+`cpa-sim` stage implementations must produce a stable `StageResult`/`PulseState` shape with explicit provenance and bounded artifact outputs so downstream tools can compare runs reproducibly.
+
+## Local instructions
+- Keep public stage I/O stable through models in `src/cpa_sim/models/`.
+- Stage modules under `src/cpa_sim/stages/` may vary internal implementation, but must emit consistent metrics/artifact references.
+- Add provenance fields for config hash, runtime/environment metadata, and stage timing without embedding large binary payloads in JSON summaries.
+- Store large arrays as files (for example `.npz`) and reference paths/keys from state/artifact metadata.
+- Any interface change requires integration tests for end-to-end stage chaining and update notes in repo docs.
+
+## Applies to
+- `src/cpa_sim/models/`
+- `src/cpa_sim/stages/`
+- CLI/reporting output paths and run artifacts
+- `tests/`
+
+## Out of scope for this repo
+- Ecosystem-level result schema ownership in `phys-pipeline`.
+- Publication/process requirements handled by the metarepo tooling.
+
+## Acceptance checks
+- [ ] `python -m pytest -q -m "not slow and not physics" --durations=10`
+- [ ] `python -m mypy src`
+- [ ] Verify metrics/artifact outputs exist in a sample CLI run.
+
+## Migration notes
+When modifying existing stage outputs, introduce compatibility adapters at stage boundaries first, then remove deprecated fields in a subsequent ADR-backed change.
