+# ADR-0003-validation-tiers-and-tolerances
+
+## Status
+Accepted
+
+## Upstream references
+- ECO-0003: `cpa-architecture/docs/adr/ECO-0003-validation-tiers-ci-policy.md` (as of 2026-02-16)
+- ECO-0001: `cpa-architecture/docs/adr/ECO-0001-conventions-units.md` (as of 2026-02-16)
+
+## Decision summary (local)
+`cpa-sim` uses explicit test tiers (`unit`, `integration`, `physics`, `slow`) with clear CI expectations so correctness claims match evidence and run-time cost.
+
+## Local instructions
+- Mark tests in `tests/` with pytest markers aligned to repo policy.
+- PR gate must run fast checks (`not slow and not physics`), while `physics`/`slow` suites are run separately (nightly/manual).
+- Changes to conventions or stage interfaces must include corresponding tests in the appropriate tier.
+- Golden/reference physics tests must pin summary metrics and tolerances; when updating tolerances, explain why in test comments/PR notes.
+- Keep validation commands and expected tiers synchronized between ADRs, AGENTS guidance, and CI configuration.
+
+## Applies to
+- `tests/`
+- CI workflow test commands for this repo
+- docs that describe validation promises (`README`, `STATUS.md`, ADRs)
+
+## Out of scope for this repo
+- Validation standards for non-`cpa-sim` repos.
+- Ecosystem governance text that does not affect this repository's test gates.
+
+## Acceptance checks
+- [ ] `python -m pytest -q -m "not slow and not physics" --durations=10`
+- [ ] `python -m pytest -q -m physics --durations=10`
+- [ ] `python -m pytest -q -m slow --durations=10`
+- [ ] `python -m pre_commit run -a`
+
+## Migration notes
+For legacy unmarked tests, progressively apply markers as files are touched; prioritize end-to-end and physics-critical tests first.
